I have successfully created the 3 required files based on your STACK, research brief, and functional spec. 

Both prototypes use a shared CSS variable system and modern aesthetic inspired by the `design-brief.md` to ensure they feel like a single coherent product. They are built entirely with plain HTML, CSS, and minimal vanilla JavaScript, relying on SVG icons to eliminate any external image dependencies.

Here is what was created:

1. **`design-brief.md`**: Outlines the unified "Stitch Integration v4" design language, including color tokens, an 8px spacing system, typography scale, component interaction states, and responsiveness guidelines.
2. **`landing-prototype.html`**: A high-converting marketing mockup featuring a hero section, feature highlights, social proof placeholders, and a transparent pricing section highlighting the freemium strategy.
3. **`app-prototype.html`**: A comprehensive, single-page application prototype. It includes minimal vanilla JavaScript to switch between all required states from your functional spec:
    *   Auth (Login, Register, Forgot Password)
    *   Dashboard Stats & Overview
    *   Invoice List & Detailed Views (with void/pay actions)
    *   Invoice Creation Form (with line items)
    *   Client Management (List & Details)
    *   Product Catalog
    *   Settings/Business Profile
    *   Interactive modals and toast notifications for feedback

You can open `landing-prototype.html` and `app-prototype.html` directly in your browser to interact with them.
